WEBVTT

00:01:05.666 --> 00:01:08.291
It's that same dream... 

00:01:08.291 --> 00:01:10.166
I always have it. 

00:01:10.166 --> 00:01:11.666
... and I always forget it.

00:01:18.958 --> 00:01:20.666
Denji

00:01:22.833 --> 00:01:24.333
Pochita!

00:01:24.333 --> 00:01:26.125
Hiding out in there, little buddy?

00:01:26.916 --> 00:01:27.750
You can at least let

00:01:27.750 --> 00:01:29.041
me pet you in my dreams.

00:01:29.625 --> 00:01:29.916
Stop.

00:01:35.708 --> 00:01:37.625
Don't open that door.

00:01:37.875 --> 00:01:38.541
No matter what.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.375
You're too loud.

00:01:59.375 --> 00:02:02.375
Seize your bile  breathing

00:02:02.375 --> 00:02:04.166
Sorry

00:02:04.166 --> 00:02:06.541
was having a nightmare that felt so...

00:02:15.250 --> 00:02:16.250
Must still be dreaming.

00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:18.083
Worm, touch me and die!

00:02:25.375 --> 00:02:26.958
What was that?

00:02:26.958 --> 00:02:28.291
This power!

00:02:28.541 --> 00:02:29.708
I am invigorated!

00:02:31.625 --> 00:02:32.500
Nope.

00:02:33.416 --> 00:02:34.666
Not a dream.

00:05:16.375 --> 00:05:17.541
interesting horns

00:05:18.666 --> 00:05:19.500
Power...

00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:21.208
looks like you drank too much blood

00:05:21.458 --> 00:05:23.333
I assume it was when you

00:05:23.333 --> 00:05:24.833
were fighting those zombies

00:05:25.791 --> 00:05:28.041
we're going to have to drain you

00:05:28.041 --> 00:05:28.833
Right!

00:05:28.833 --> 00:05:29.708
Say what?

00:05:30.416 --> 00:05:32.083
Every once in a while, Power needs to

00:05:32.083 --> 00:05:32.958
have her blood drained.

00:05:32.958 --> 00:05:34.791
Otherwise, her ego grows frightening.

00:05:36.208 --> 00:05:37.875
She's far more selfish than usual.

00:05:38.583 --> 00:05:40.000
So do you mind, Denji?

00:05:41.041 --> 00:05:42.791
Can I borrow Power for a bit?

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:51.416
You can have her as long as you want.

00:05:53.500 --> 00:05:54.750
In the meantime, you'll

00:05:54.750 --> 00:05:55.958
need a substitute partner.

00:05:55.958 --> 00:05:57.750
Luckily, there's someone

00:05:57.750 --> 00:05:59.083
keen to team up with you.

00:06:04.583 --> 00:06:06.458
What a glorious honor!

00:06:11.125 --> 00:06:13.375
Can't I get a normal partner, like ever?

00:06:13.958 --> 00:06:15.375
That's the shark fiend.

00:06:15.916 --> 00:06:17.583
Typically, he's so ferocious it's

00:06:17.583 --> 00:06:18.833
impossible to talk to him.

00:06:19.625 --> 00:06:20.500
He said he'll be a good

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:21.625
boy and obey you, though.

00:06:22.875 --> 00:06:24.000
How does that make any sense?

00:06:24.625 --> 00:06:25.208
Why me?

00:06:25.208 --> 00:06:26.458
I have no idea.

00:06:27.083 --> 00:06:29.250
You do share a passing resemblance.

00:06:29.250 --> 00:06:30.958
you knew I'll serve you good!

00:06:30.958 --> 00:06:32.250
No matter what you ask!

00:06:32.250 --> 00:06:33.125
You're the best!

00:06:33.125 --> 00:06:33.750
The greatest!

00:06:34.083 --> 00:06:35.208
A righteous badass!

00:06:35.416 --> 00:06:37.125
I'm not really into dudes, alright?

00:06:37.375 --> 00:06:37.791
Mm-hmm.

00:06:42.583 --> 00:06:42.750
Hmm?

00:06:44.125 --> 00:06:45.875
You don't seem thrilled about this.

00:06:45.875 --> 00:06:49.500
I've never been more excited.

00:06:54.208 --> 00:06:55.583
If that's really the case,

00:06:55.583 --> 00:06:56.625
then we should go on a date.

00:06:56.958 --> 00:06:58.541
We do both have tomorrow off.

00:06:59.541 --> 00:07:00.375
A date?

00:07:00.375 --> 00:07:04.916
Hell yeah!

00:07:05.291 --> 00:07:06.333
Hell yeah!

00:07:07.583 --> 00:07:07.791
Hell yeah!

00:07:09.583 --> 00:07:10.208
Denji?

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:12.375
I didn't expect to see you here yet.

00:07:13.416 --> 00:07:14.291
You're an hour early.

00:07:14.291 --> 00:07:21.000
So cute!

00:07:21.750 --> 00:07:23.708
I hope you haven't been

00:07:23.708 --> 00:07:24.916
waiting around very long.

00:07:24.916 --> 00:07:26.000
Just since 5am.

00:07:26.041 --> 00:07:26.875
I couldn't sleep.

00:07:27.583 --> 00:07:28.791
So, uh, what are you

00:07:28.791 --> 00:07:30.125
thinking we should get into today?

00:07:30.833 --> 00:07:33.416
You know, uh, I've technically never hung

00:07:33.416 --> 00:07:34.291
out with a girl before.

00:07:34.291 --> 00:07:36.291
My plans for the day will

00:07:36.291 --> 00:07:37.416
keep us busy through midnight.

00:07:38.250 --> 00:07:38.916
You and I are going

00:07:38.916 --> 00:07:40.083
to do a movie marathon.

00:07:42.083 --> 00:07:42.375
What?

00:07:42.375 --> 00:07:42.583
What?

00:07:52.416 --> 00:07:52.833
Damn.

00:07:53.958 --> 00:07:54.708
This isn't how I was

00:07:54.708 --> 00:07:56.000
hoping things would play out.

00:07:56.291 --> 00:07:57.750
You will not prevail!

00:08:00.166 --> 00:08:00.791
Everyone's laughing.

00:08:01.625 --> 00:08:03.000
But it's not even funny.

00:08:09.291 --> 00:08:10.708
Miss Malkima's not laughing either.

00:08:11.916 --> 00:08:12.791
Damn, she's cute.

00:08:15.125 --> 00:08:16.333
Was I supposed to be

00:08:16.333 --> 00:08:17.250
bored out of my skull?

00:08:17.750 --> 00:08:19.291
Probably not, but I'm with you.

00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:20.666
Looked like they spent a

00:08:20.666 --> 00:08:21.750
lot of money making it, too.

00:08:23.708 --> 00:08:24.083
Oh, well.

00:08:24.833 --> 00:08:26.041
Let's head to the next film.

00:08:32.833 --> 00:08:33.250
Hmm?

00:08:37.208 --> 00:08:38.208
Everyone's crying.

00:08:41.166 --> 00:08:41.958
But she's not.

00:08:42.916 --> 00:08:43.166
Cute.

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:46.791
That one sucked, too.

00:08:47.333 --> 00:08:48.875
Yeah, and I hated how hard they were

00:08:48.875 --> 00:08:50.416
trying to make the audience cry.

00:08:50.416 --> 00:08:56.833
At least the music was memorable.

00:08:57.500 --> 00:08:58.208
Ah!

00:08:59.791 --> 00:09:01.541
I didn't think the story was believable.

00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:08.416
That one was mediocre at best.

00:09:09.125 --> 00:09:10.083
One more to go.

00:09:10.083 --> 00:09:14.375
From what I hear, people find this film

00:09:14.375 --> 00:09:16.000
difficult to wrap their heads around.

00:09:16.333 --> 00:09:17.833
I hope you don't mind too much.

00:09:20.666 --> 00:09:21.416
I don't know.

00:09:22.041 --> 00:09:24.083
Everything we've seen
was a crap fest.

00:09:24.083 --> 00:09:27.291
maybe I just don't understand movies

00:09:27.291 --> 00:09:32.375
Well, I usually only enjoy one out of every ten films I sit through.

00:09:32.375 --> 00:09:41.583
Thing is, I believe that a single good movie can change your entire life.

00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:29.000
What the? No, no stupid eyes. You can't

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:32.333
cry on a first date. Shit. I hope Miss

00:10:32.333 --> 00:10:33.583
Makima doesn't see this.

00:10:50.208 --> 00:10:53.208
Man, I won't forget the

00:10:53.208 --> 00:10:54.875
last scene as long as I live.

00:10:55.208 --> 00:10:57.625
Me neither. That movie alone was worth

00:10:57.625 --> 00:10:59.041
every ticket we bought today.

00:11:01.625 --> 00:11:04.666
Hmm. So, uh, Miss Makima,

00:11:05.041 --> 00:11:07.375
do you think I have a heart?

00:11:07.375 --> 00:11:09.750
Why ask me that, don't you know?

00:11:09.750 --> 00:11:12.041
I was just wondering.

00:11:35.166 --> 00:11:39.041
Yes, you do

00:11:39.041 --> 00:11:47.166
I do.

00:12:10.416 --> 00:12:14.833
She put her head on me and I thought butterflies had burst out.

00:12:14.833 --> 00:12:19.041
That means I gotta have a heart.

00:12:19.041 --> 00:12:24.708
Hi. We're collecting donations for children who've been impacted by devil attacks. Anything helps! 

00:12:24.708 --> 00:12:28.625
As a guy with a heart, you bet I'm helping.

00:12:28.625 --> 00:12:30.958
Your support means the world.

00:12:30.958 --> 00:12:34.500
And to show you our gratitude, we want you to have this flower.

00:12:37.583 --> 00:12:39.333
Nice

00:12:45.291 --> 00:12:47.541
I can appreciate a good flower.

00:12:47.541 --> 00:12:50.041
More proof my chest ain't hollow.

00:12:52.916 --> 00:12:54.083
Ms. Makima is incredible.
 

00:12:55.083 --> 00:12:58.333
I feel like a brand new man, 
after talking to her

00:12:59.875 --> 00:13:04.541
She said she'll grant me a wish once I've gathered a bunch of pieces of the gun devil.

00:13:04.541 --> 00:13:07.541
When that happens, I'm gonna ask her to be my girlfriend.

00:13:19.166 --> 00:13:22.166
Yeah, she's in my head every second I'm not saw deep in a devil.

00:13:22.166 --> 00:13:25.166
I may have squeezed another girl's boobs and I got to make out once.

00:13:25.166 --> 00:13:28.166
But my heart is the property of Ms. Makima. 

00:13:28.875 --> 00:13:31.875
There's no way I'm ever gonna fall for another woman.

00:13:40.541 --> 00:13:43.541
Water! Water! Yeah!

00:13:47.041 --> 00:13:50.041
Beam. You're supposed to stay hidden, dude.

00:13:50.041 --> 00:13:52.583
If you cause a scene, we're going to have to start sneaking around.

00:13:52.583 --> 00:13:55.583
Right

00:13:55.583 --> 00:13:58.583
Why do you fiends always got to have such dumbass names anyway?

00:14:12.625 --> 00:14:15.625
Should have brought an umbrella with me.

00:14:26.291 --> 00:14:32.833
Hiya, tight fit. It's really coming down

00:14:32.833 --> 00:14:35.541
out there. I'm soaked.

00:14:36.041 --> 00:14:37.583
This wasn't in the forecast.

00:14:44.125 --> 00:14:45.541
Huh?

00:14:45.541 --> 00:14:46.833
Are you good?

00:14:47.416 --> 00:14:48.125
Oops.

00:14:48.416 --> 00:14:51.083
Sorry. Ignore me.

00:14:51.708 --> 00:14:53.041
I don't see what's so funny.

00:14:57.333 --> 00:14:58.916
Crap, are you crying now?

00:14:59.583 --> 00:15:03.083
I can't help it. My dog died recently.

00:15:03.083 --> 00:15:05.833
And your face, you look just like him.

00:15:06.125 --> 00:15:07.208
Hold up, so I look like a

00:15:07.208 --> 00:15:08.625
damn mud is what you're saying?

00:15:09.166 --> 00:15:12.583
No, it's not like that. I'm sorry.

00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:20.125
Oh, jeez, are you okay?

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:28.208
I've got a handkerchief here somewhere.

00:15:29.708 --> 00:15:31.875
Ta-da!

00:15:32.416 --> 00:15:37.875
What? Is that magic? You're amazing.

00:15:39.041 --> 00:15:41.708
Just be your gag reflex.

00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:50.041
Thanks for the flower.

00:16:00.166 --> 00:16:02.958
Look, the rain stopped.

00:16:02.958 --> 00:16:05.416
I work at a cafe called Crossroads. It's

00:16:05.416 --> 00:16:07.375
not too far away from here.

00:16:07.375 --> 00:16:08.416
If you drop by, I'll

00:16:08.416 --> 00:16:09.333
pay you back somehow.

00:16:09.333 --> 00:16:10.708
Come see me, okay?

00:16:53.833 --> 00:16:54.500
Yes.

00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:55.291
About time you got here.

00:16:55.291 --> 00:16:57.916
I'm docking your pay for being late.

00:16:57.916 --> 00:16:59.250
That is so not cool.

00:16:59.250 --> 00:17:00.916
Go on, take this to table four.

00:17:00.916 --> 00:17:02.375
If you weren't so cheap, you'd cut your

00:17:02.375 --> 00:17:03.666
best server some slack.

00:17:08.041 --> 00:17:08.625
You.

00:17:08.625 --> 00:17:10.375
That was fast.

00:17:10.375 --> 00:17:11.750
You are magic.

00:17:11.750 --> 00:17:13.500
It makes no sense you beat me.

00:17:14.333 --> 00:17:15.916
It seemed like a good place to dry off.

00:17:17.708 --> 00:17:19.166
So, you said you would pay me back.

00:17:25.625 --> 00:17:27.291
How about we have a drink together?

00:17:28.458 --> 00:17:29.541
Bossman, over here!

00:17:29.541 --> 00:17:31.166
A couple of coffees, if you don't mind.

00:17:31.750 --> 00:17:33.458
You're the waitress here, not me.

00:17:34.208 --> 00:17:35.750
Sheesh, don't be so rude.

00:17:35.750 --> 00:17:38.166
Besides, we only ever get customers in the morning.

00:17:41.041 --> 00:17:42.208
Fine.

00:17:44.125 --> 00:17:45.083
My gift to you.

00:17:45.083 --> 00:17:45.375
Enjoy!

00:17:46.250 --> 00:17:48.416
You like coffee, don't you?

00:17:48.416 --> 00:17:49.375
I'll drink it.

00:17:55.208 --> 00:17:56.375
What's that face for?

00:17:56.375 --> 00:17:57.708
It can't be that bad, can it?

00:17:57.708 --> 00:17:58.416
Yeah, huh.

00:17:58.416 --> 00:18:00.208
Coffee tastes like gutter water.

00:18:00.500 --> 00:18:01.916
Brewed in the crapper.

00:18:04.791 --> 00:18:06.791
You sound like a little kid.

00:18:09.500 --> 00:18:11.375
She sure is touching me a lot.

00:18:11.375 --> 00:18:13.333
And laughing at my jokes.

00:18:13.333 --> 00:18:14.708
Is it possible that...

00:18:16.166 --> 00:18:17.750
This girl is into me?

00:18:18.666 --> 00:18:19.958
I'm Reze, by the way.

00:18:19.958 --> 00:18:21.041
And you?

00:18:21.041 --> 00:18:21.625
Flower boy?

00:18:22.916 --> 00:18:24.083
I'm Denji.

00:18:24.083 --> 00:18:25.125
Oh, Denji.

00:18:32.083 --> 00:18:33.333
I've never met anyone

00:18:33.333 --> 00:18:34.416
as interesting as you.

00:18:34.416 --> 00:18:35.583
It's pretty great.

00:18:38.875 --> 00:18:39.875
Holy hell.

00:18:40.458 --> 00:18:42.666
She is definitely into me.

00:18:42.666 --> 00:18:43.708
What do I do?

00:18:43.708 --> 00:18:46.583
When someone likes me, I

00:18:46.583 --> 00:18:48.625
can't help but like them back.

00:18:48.625 --> 00:18:49.791
Save me, Miss Makima.

00:18:50.583 --> 00:18:51.916
Give me strength.

00:18:51.916 --> 00:18:54.750
Otherwise, I'm gonna fall for this girl.

00:19:11.625 --> 00:19:12.625
You've downed three of

00:19:12.625 --> 00:19:13.833
those in a row, you addict.

00:19:13.833 --> 00:19:15.125
It's time for us to go patrol.

00:19:16.541 --> 00:19:18.458
All this ice cream's got me tired.

00:19:18.458 --> 00:19:21.000
I never realized that eating could take

00:19:21.000 --> 00:19:22.208
so much energy out of you.

00:19:26.583 --> 00:19:27.916
I'm afraid I've lost the

00:19:27.916 --> 00:19:29.291
will to work anymore today.

00:19:31.375 --> 00:19:33.000
Now that we know where the gun devil is,

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:33.875
there'll be an expedition.

00:19:33.875 --> 00:19:35.750
I need more experience defeating powerful

00:19:35.750 --> 00:19:37.333
devils if I want to get in on it.

00:19:39.416 --> 00:19:40.500
So I have to hunt.

00:19:40.500 --> 00:19:41.333
It's the only way for

00:19:41.333 --> 00:19:43.083
me to get my numbers up.

00:19:43.083 --> 00:19:44.333
You're my partner.

00:19:44.333 --> 00:19:46.416
Please, help me out.

00:19:54.916 --> 00:19:57.250
Well, if you buy me another cone, I could

00:19:57.250 --> 00:20:00.583
take it under consideration.

00:20:00.583 --> 00:20:01.250
Get up.

00:20:02.041 --> 00:20:03.166
Otherwise, I'll have to

00:20:03.166 --> 00:20:04.375
tell leadership you're useless.

00:20:04.375 --> 00:20:06.333
As a devil, they'll slaughter you.

00:20:06.333 --> 00:20:08.958
Is that what you want?

00:20:15.458 --> 00:20:16.500
Dying sounds like way more fun than

00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:18.333
working, to be honest.

00:20:21.416 --> 00:20:23.708
He's the strongest member of Division 4

00:20:23.708 --> 00:20:25.666
after Captain Kishibe.

00:20:26.333 --> 00:20:27.750
Or at least he would be if

00:20:27.750 --> 00:20:29.583
he weren't always so lazy.

00:20:30.125 --> 00:20:32.458
If you want to join the operation to

00:20:32.458 --> 00:20:34.083
defeat the gun devil, I suggest you try

00:20:34.083 --> 00:20:35.708
to play nice with him.

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:38.375
I don't think I can

00:20:38.375 --> 00:20:39.791
work well with a devil.

00:20:40.833 --> 00:20:42.541
You say that, but haven't you and Power

00:20:42.541 --> 00:20:44.416
been getting on better?

00:20:44.416 --> 00:20:45.666
Are you kidding?

00:20:45.666 --> 00:20:47.708
We had a fist fight just this morning.

00:20:49.458 --> 00:20:51.208
I'm not saying the two of you have to

00:20:51.208 --> 00:20:52.500
become best friends.

00:20:52.500 --> 00:20:54.000
Only that you can use

00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:55.375
him for your own benefit.

00:20:56.250 --> 00:20:58.333
You'd be interested to know that he

00:20:58.333 --> 00:20:59.583
killed every single person in

00:20:59.583 --> 00:21:00.958
the village where he was born.

00:21:00.958 --> 00:21:03.666
Or more accurately, he siphoned off their

00:21:03.666 --> 00:21:06.083
lifespans and turned them into weapons.

00:21:07.291 --> 00:21:08.000
Weapons?

00:21:09.083 --> 00:21:11.000
He can transform the life of anyone he

00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:12.083
touches into a weapon.

00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:14.125
In fact, the sword you

00:21:14.125 --> 00:21:16.166
wield is one of his creations.

00:21:16.166 --> 00:21:18.416
They can do things like cut

00:21:18.416 --> 00:21:19.625
through intangible ghosts.

00:21:19.625 --> 00:21:21.750
Each one has some sort of unique ability.

00:21:24.708 --> 00:21:26.875
You can always just

00:21:26.875 --> 00:21:28.250
pretend to get along with him.

00:21:28.250 --> 00:21:28.958
Try to be friendly and I

00:21:28.958 --> 00:21:29.958
bet he'll come in handy.

00:21:50.083 --> 00:21:52.583
I've eliminated the devil!

00:21:52.583 --> 00:21:53.500
Stay inside!

00:21:53.500 --> 00:21:54.791
Make sure not to touch

00:21:54.791 --> 00:21:56.625
his flesh or its blood!

00:22:03.458 --> 00:22:03.916
Yummy.

00:22:03.916 --> 00:22:04.458
Looks delicious.

00:22:07.833 --> 00:22:09.166
One moment, Eamon.

00:22:09.166 --> 00:22:10.125
Get back over here.

00:22:12.333 --> 00:22:14.416
This guy must be a civilian devil hunter.

00:22:14.416 --> 00:22:16.333
He's missing his bottom half.

00:22:16.333 --> 00:22:17.791
Probably eaten recently.

00:22:19.958 --> 00:22:21.458
Anyway, he'll die soon.

00:22:25.708 --> 00:22:27.000
Kill me.

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:27.791
Kill me.

00:22:27.791 --> 00:22:28.000
Kill me.

00:22:28.166 --> 00:22:28.625
Please.

00:22:30.208 --> 00:22:31.000
Grant him his wish.

00:22:31.541 --> 00:22:32.708
If you use your power,

